caption: Very tasty food! The food is gluten free

went to Dekalb market Hall and my favorite place was closed. somebody suggested I try the new African spot TERANGA I was surprise there was a new spot there. I said why not, As it would turn out the best kept secret at Dekalb market Hall. relatively new, they pretty much started doing th pandemic and surprisingly they're doing OK. they are hanging in there. food was great. service was exceptional, fast ,friendly. and I love the fact that they are green w/there to go packages. I can't wait to go back. Love this place....🙏😊👍🏽😚🤟🏾😍
Awesome food!  Love that they "think green" with the food and beverages they serve and the "order to go"  cutlery and bowls.

I got the vegan bowl with a medium spicy hot sauce, and it was delicious (fyi I am not vegan). The portion size was huge, and the food was hearty, comforting, and flavorful with a range of contrasting flavors and textures. Would highly recommend!

I just came across this stall today and got a casamance bowl, morninga limeade, and sombi coconut rice pudding. All were great, and was supposed to share the pudding—but it was so good, I forgot to! Going back tomorrow for more.
